    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-08-26T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-08-26T17:00:00-05:00" n="445"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d445">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.00 Revolutions/340: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MEV1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-08-26T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 26, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>69. Your telegram No. 90 of August 22, 2 p.m. Please report promptly details of
                    any case which may arise involving an application of the proclamation in
                    question to an American citizen or interest. Also cable the date of the law
                    establishing the monopoly and transmit a copy of the law by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CWR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
